Renames all `Rule`s if this is a [`ParsingError`]. It does nothing when called on a
 [`CustomError`].

defs.name: iterators
defs.docs: Types and iterators for parser output.

defs.name: FlatPairs
defs.docs: An iterator over [`Pair`]s. It is created by [`Pairs::flatten`].

defs.name: tokens
defs.docs: Returns the `Tokens` for these pairs.

defs.name: Pair
defs.docs: A matching pair of [`Token`]s and everything between them.

defs.name: as_rule
defs.docs: Returns the `Rule` of the `Pair`.

defs.name: as_str
defs.docs: Captures a slice from the `&str` defined by the token `Pair`.

defs.name: into_span
defs.docs: Returns the `Span` defined by the `Pair`, consuming it.

defs.name: as_span
defs.docs: Returns the `Span` defined by the `Pair`, **without** consuming it.

defs.name: into_inner
defs.docs: Returns the inner `Pairs` between the `Pair`, consuming it.

defs.name: tokens
defs.docs: Returns the `Tokens` for the `Pair`.

defs.name: Pairs
defs.docs: An iterator over [`Pair`]s. It is created by [`pest::state`] and [`Pair::into_inner`].

defs.name: as_str
defs.docs:
Captures a slice from the `&str` defined by the starting position of the first token `Pair`
 and the ending position of the last token `Pair` of the `Pairs`. This also captures
 the input between those two token `Pair`s.

defs.name: concat
defs.docs:
Captures inner token `Pair`s and concatenates resulting `&str`s. This does not capture
 the input between token `Pair`s.

defs.name: flatten
defs.docs: Flattens the `Pairs`.

defs.name: tokens
defs.docs: Returns the `Tokens` for the `Pairs`.

defs.name: peek
defs.docs: Peek at the first inner `Pair` without changing the position of this iterator.

defs.name: Tokens
defs.docs: An iterator over [`Token`]s. It is created by [`Pair::tokens`] and [`Pairs::tokens`].

defs.name: Parser
defs.docs: A trait with a single method that parses strings.

defs.name: parse
defs.docs: Parses a `&str` starting from `rule`.

defs.name: Lookahead
defs.docs: The current lookahead status of a [`ParserState`].

defs.name: Atomicity
defs.docs: The current atomicity of a [`ParserState`].

defs.name: ParseResult
defs.docs: Type alias to simplify specifying the return value of chained closures.

defs.name: MatchDir
defs.docs: Match direction for the stack. Used in `PEEK[a..b]`/`stack_match_peek_slice`.

defs.name: ParserState
defs.docs: The complete state of a [`Parser`].

defs.name: state
defs.value: fn <'i, R, F> (input: &'i str, f: F) -> Result<pairs::Pairs<'i, R>, Error<R>>
defs.docs: Creates a `ParserState` from a `&str`, supplying it to a closure `f`.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Allocates a fresh `ParserState` object to the heap and returns the owned `Box`. This `Box`
 will be passed from closure to closure based on the needs of the specified `Parser`.

defs.name: position
defs.docs: Returns a reference to the current `Position` of the `ParserState`.

defs.name: atomicity
defs.docs: Returns the current atomicity of the `ParserState`.

defs.name: rule
defs.value: fn <F> (mut self: Box<Self>, rule: R, f: F) -> ParseResult<Box<Self>>
defs.docs:
Wrapper needed to generate tokens. This will associate the `R` type rule to the closure
 meant to match the rule.

defs.name: sequence
defs.docs:
Starts a sequence of transformations provided by `f` from the `Box<ParserState>`. Returns
 the same `Result` returned by `f` in the case of an `Ok`, or `Err` with the current
 `Box<ParserState>` otherwise.

defs.name: repeat
defs.value: fn <F> (self: Box<Self>, mut f: F) -> ParseResult<Box<Self>>
defs.docs:
Repeatedly applies the transformation provided by `f` from the `Box<ParserState>`. Returns
 `Ok` with the updated `Box<ParserState>` returned by `f` wrapped up in an `Err`.

defs.name: optional
defs.docs:
Optionally applies the transformation provided by `f` from the `Box<ParserState>`. Returns
 `Ok` with the updated `Box<ParserState>` returned by `f` regardless of the `Result`.

defs.name: match_char_by
defs.value: fn <F> (mut self: Box<Self>, f: F) -> ParseResult<Box<Self>>
defs.docs:
Attempts to match a single character based on a filter function. Returns `Ok` with the
 updated `Box<ParserState>` if successful, or `Err` with the updated `Box<ParserState>`
 otherwise.

defs.name: match_string
defs.docs:
Attempts to match the given string. Returns `Ok` with the updated `Box<ParserState>` if
 successful, or `Err` with the updated `Box<ParserState>` otherwise.

defs.name: match_insensitive
defs.docs:
Attempts to case-insensitively match the given string. Returns `Ok` with the updated
 `Box<ParserState>` if successful, or `Err` with the updated `Box<ParserState>` otherwise.

defs.name: match_range
defs.value: fn (mut self: Box<Self>, range: Range<char>) -> ParseResult<Box<Self>>
defs.docs:
Attempts to match a single character from the given range. Returns `Ok` with the updated
 `Box<ParserState>` if successful, or `Err` with the updated `Box<ParserState>` otherwise.

defs.name: skip
defs.value: fn (mut self: Box<Self>, n: usize) -> ParseResult<Box<Self>>
defs.docs:
Attempts to skip `n` characters forward. Returns `Ok` with the updated `Box<ParserState>`
 if successful, or `Err` with the updated `Box<ParserState>` otherwise.

defs.name: skip_until
defs.docs:
Attempts to skip forward until one of the given strings is found. Returns `Ok` with the
 updated `Box<ParserState>` whether or not one of the strings is found.

defs.name: start_of_input
defs.docs:
Attempts to match the start of the input. Returns `Ok` with the current `Box<ParserState>`
 if the parser has not yet advanced, or `Err` with the current `Box<ParserState>` otherwise.

defs.name: end_of_input
defs.docs:
Attempts to match the end of the input. Returns `Ok` with the current `Box<ParserState>` if
 there is no input remaining, or `Err` with the current `Box<ParserState>` otherwise.

defs.name: lookahead
defs.value: fn <F> (mut self: Box<Self>, is_positive: bool, f: F) -> ParseResult<Box<Self>>
defs.docs:
Starts a lookahead transformation provided by `f` from the `Box<ParserState>`. It returns
 `Ok` with the current `Box<ParserState>` if `f` also returns an `Ok`, or `Err` with the current
 `Box<ParserState>` otherwise. If `is_positive` is `false`, it swaps the `Ok` and `Err`
 together, negating the `Result`.

defs.name: atomic
defs.value: fn <F> (mut self: Box<Self>, atomicity: Atomicity, f: F) -> ParseResult<Box<Self>>
defs.docs: Transformation which stops `Token`s from being generated according to `is_atomic`.

defs.name: stack_push
defs.docs:
Evaluates the result of closure `f` and pushes the span of the input consumed from before
 `f` is called to after `f` is called to the stack. Returns `Ok(Box<ParserState>)` if `f` is
 called successfully, or `Err(Box<ParserState>)` otherwise.

defs.name: stack_peek
defs.docs:
Peeks the top of the stack and attempts to match the string. Returns `Ok(Box<ParserState>)`
 if the string is matched successfully, or `Err(Box<ParserState>)` otherwise.

defs.name: stack_pop
defs.docs:
Pops the top of the stack and attempts to match the string. Returns `Ok(Box<ParserState>)`
 if the string is matched successfully, or `Err(Box<ParserState>)` otherwise.

defs.name: stack_match_peek_slice
defs.value: fn (mut self: Box<Self>, start: i32, end: Option<i32>, match_dir: MatchDir) -> ParseResult<Box<Self>>
defs.docs: Matches part of the state of the stack.

defs.name: stack_match_peek
defs.docs: Matches the full state of the stack.

defs.name: stack_match_pop
defs.docs: Matches the full state of the stack. This method will clear the stack as it evaluates.

defs.name: stack_drop
defs.docs:
Drops the top of the stack. Returns `Ok(Box<ParserState>)` if there was a value to drop, or
 `Err(Box<ParserState>)` otherwise.

defs.name: restore_on_err
defs.docs:
Restores the original state of the `ParserState` when `f` returns an `Err`. Currently,
 this method only restores the stack.

defs.name: Position
defs.docs: A cursor position in a `&str` which provides useful methods to manually parse that string.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Attempts to create a new `Position` at the given position. If the specified position is
 an invalid index, or the specified position is not a valid UTF8 boundary, then None is
 returned.

defs.name: from_start
defs.docs: Creates a `Position` at the start of a `&str`.

defs.name: pos
defs.docs: Returns the byte position of this `Position` as a `usize`.

defs.name: span
defs.docs: Creates a `Span` from two `Position`s.

defs.name: line_col
defs.docs: Returns the line and column number of this `Position`.

defs.name: line_of
defs.docs: Returns the entire line of the input that contains this `Position`.

defs.name: prec_climber
defs.docs: Constructs useful in infix operator parsing with the precedence climbing method.

defs.name: Left
defs.docs: Left `Operator` associativity

defs.name: Right
defs.docs: Right `Operator` associativity

defs.name: Assoc
defs.docs: Associativity of an [`Operator`].

defs.name: Operator
defs.docs: Infix operator used in [`PrecClimber`].

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates a new `Operator` from a `Rule` and `Assoc`.

defs.name: PrecClimber
defs.docs:
List of operators and precedences, which can perform [precedence climbing][1] on infix
 expressions contained in a [`Pairs`]. The token pairs contained in the `Pairs` should start
 with a *primary* pair and then alternate between an *operator* and a *primary*.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Creates a new `PrecClimber` from the `Operator`s contained in `ops`. Every entry in the
 `Vec` has precedence *index + 1*. In order to have operators with same precedence, they need
 to be chained with `|` between them.

defs.name: climb
defs.value: fn <'i, P, F, G, T> (&self, mut pairs: P, mut primary: F, mut infix: G) -> T
defs.docs:
Performs the precedence climbing algorithm on the `pairs` in a similar manner to map-reduce.
 *Primary* pairs are mapped with `primary` and then reduced to one single result with
 `infix`.

defs.name: Span
defs.docs: A span over a `&str`. It is created from either [two `Position`s] or from a [`Pair`].

defs.name: new
defs.value: fn (input: &str, start: usize, end: usize) -> Option<Span>
defs.docs:
Attempts to create a new span. Will return `None` if `input[start..end]` is an invalid index
 into `input`.

defs.name: start
defs.docs: Returns the `Span`'s start byte position as a `usize`.

defs.name: end
defs.docs: Returns the `Span`'s end byte position as a `usize`.

defs.name: start_pos
defs.docs: Returns the `Span`'s start `Position`.

defs.name: end_pos
defs.docs: Returns the `Span`'s end `Position`.

defs.name: split
defs.docs: Splits the `Span` into a pair of `Position`s.

defs.name: as_str
defs.docs: Captures a slice from the `&str` defined by the `Span`.

defs.name: lines
defs.docs: Iterates over all lines (partially) covered by this span.

defs.name: Lines
defs.docs: Line iterator for Spans, created by [`Span::lines()`].

defs.name: Start
defs.docs: The starting `Position` of a matched `Rule`

defs.name: End
defs.docs: The ending `Position` of a matched `Rule`

defs.docs: A token generated by a `Parser`.
